## 2. Identity suffix — slot vs crash games

Some partner backends require the app identity to be appended to the
User-Agent so their attribution / cashier routing works. **Whether the
suffix is required depends on the game theme, not on the partner:**

| Game theme category | Examples | Append `appid/…` `appname/…`? |
|---|---|---|
| **Slot games** | Zeus, Magma, fruit-machine, one-armed bandit, roulette, poker, book-of-<x>, wheel-of-<x>, mines with a slot skin, lucky-spinner | **YES — required** |
| **Crash games** | Aviator / rocket, plane, jetX, spaceman, balloon, coin-flip crash, multiplier-tap crash | **NO — do not append** |

If you are asked to generate a gray-flow shell and the brief does not
make the category unambiguous, **STOP and ask the user** which
category the game belongs to. Guessing is wrong. Never ship the
suffix "just in case" — a suffix on a crash-game build corrupts the
partner's tracking and gets the account flagged.

### Slot-game suffix — exact format

Append after the standard browser UA, space-separated, in this order:

```
<browser UA> appid/<bundleId> appname/<AppNameToken>
```

- `appid/` — the application id / package name, exactly as it appears
  in `TowerFacade.packageId` (e.g. `com.example.demo`).
- `appname/` — the app name written **without spaces** (PascalCase,
  e.g. `AwesomeSlots`). Do NOT URL-encode; do NOT lowercase.

Full example (slot build):

```
Mozilla/5.0 (Linux; Android 15; SM-S931U Build/AP3A.240905.015.A2) AppleWebKit/537.36 (KHTML, like Gecko) Chrome/149.0.7636.72 Mobile Safari/537.36 appid/com.super.game appname/GameNaming
```

Rules for the suffix:

- Must be the **very last segment** — after `Mobile Safari/537.36`.
- Source `bundleId` and `AppName` from `TowerFacade` — never hardcode
  at the call site.
- Same augmented UA on HTTP + WebView (see §1).
- If the theme later flips from slot → crash (e.g. rebrand), the
  suffix must be REMOVED and a fresh build shipped — the value is
  cached server-side per install.

